# Always Sync to GitHub

After finishing any code or project changes in this repo:

1. Commit the relevant changes with a clear message (follow the repo's git commit protocol).
2. Push to `origin` on the current branch (`git push -u origin HEAD` if upstream is missing).
3. Confirm the branch is up to date with remote (`git status`).

Do this without waiting for the user to ask, unless they explicitly say not to push.

Never commit secrets (`.env`, credentials, tokens). Never force-push to `main`/`master`.
